PREAMBLE : This week head to Charlotte Motor Speedway's "Road" layout. A combination of the twisty infield with a challenging uphill corner, and 3/4 of the full oval makes for great racing. The strong draft around the oval section will lead to a lot of last-lap strategy - do you wait behind the leader to pass on the oval, or try to lead out the whole last lap? 
TRACK_NOTES : \
[color=red][b]IMPORTANT:[/b][/color] The pit lane exits [i]directly[/i] onto the inside of turn one! PLEASE make sure to check for oncoming traffic before exiting!
[youtube]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FlYIqRIuS3s[/youtube]

[color=red][b]IMPORTANT:[/b][/color]The white line at the bottom of the banking defines the edge of the 'racing surface', according to iRacing staff. Do not run below this line attempting to 'shortcut' the corners. Even though you will not get a 1x this *is* a protestable violation of the Sporting Code.
